===============================================================================

Blazer::Querygen has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Set your OpenAI API key as an environment variable:
   export OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

   Or add to .env file:
   OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

2. Configure the initializer if needed:
   config/initializers/blazer_querygen.rb

3. Blazer layout has been generated:

   The generator created app/views/layouts/blazer/application.html.erb
   which includes the AI query generation UI using the helper method:

     <%= blazer_querygen_javascript %>

   Benefits of using the helper method:
   - Only loads JavaScript when OpenAI API key is configured
   - Gracefully handles asset loading errors
   - Prevents JavaScript errors on pages without proper configuration

   Alternative: If you prefer to add it to your own layout:

     <%= blazer_querygen_javascript %>

   Note: This overrides Blazer's default layout to include our JavaScript.

4. Restart your Rails server:
   rails restart

5. Navigate to Blazer's "New Query" page and you'll see the AI generation UI!

Troubleshooting:
- If JavaScript doesn't load, check browser console for errors
- Verify OPENAI_API_KEY is set: rails c > ENV['OPENAI_API_KEY']
- Check health endpoint: /blazer/querygen/health

For more information, visit:
https://github.com/SonicGarden/blazer-querygen

===============================================================================
